definitions: (of a book, journal, piece of music, etc.) prepared and issued for public sale or readership

examples.text: the collection includes the complete published works of Benjamin Britten
thirty-one published articles were reviewed for potential inclusion

shortDefinitions: (of book etc.) prepared and issued for public sale

definitions: (of a writer) having had a work prepared and issued for public sale or readership

examples.text: a course that offers the opportunity to have your writing critiqued by a published author
Franco is also a published novelist and poet

shortDefinitions: having had work prepared and issued for public sale

definitions: (of information) printed or made available online so as to be generally known

examples.text: there is very little published data on the subject

shortDefinitions: (of information) printed or made available online
